<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Training Pact Signed With Bangladesh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2702103394 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2702103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Republic of Singapore Air Force [RSAF] can now 
train in Bangladesh. The two countries today signed a memorandum 
of understanding [MOU] and the implementation of long-term 
training. Under this, the RSAF is allowed to deploy a number of 
aircraft at Bangladesh Air Force bases for several months a year. 
  Mindef [Ministry of Defense] says Singapore welcomes the 
move 
by Dhaka. It said the increased interaction between the two air 
forces will contribute to stronger defense ties. 
  The MOU was signed in Singapore by the Chief of Air Force 
Brigadier General Bey Soo Khiang and Air Vice Marshal Altaf 
Hossain Chowdhury, Chief of Air Staff of the Bangladesh Air 
Force. 

</TEXT>

