<H3> <TI>   Turk's Wellington Contacts, News Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103144294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, who is on an 
official visit in New Zealand, has concluded his contacts in 
Wellington. Yasar Kefeli from the Turkish Radio and Television 
team in Wellington reports the following: 
  [Begin Kefeli recording] The significant role New Zealand, a 
UN Security Council member, can play in the solution of regional 
issues such as Bosnia-Herzegovina and Karabakh was discussed at 
the talks Cetin held in Wellington. The restructuring of the UN 
Security Council and how it can become more effective were also 
discussed at the talks. Cetin was also received by New Zealand 
Prime Minister Jim Bolger. He also met with Donald Charles 
McKinnon, New Zealand deputy prime minister and minister of 
external relations and trade. 
  Later official talks were held between the two delegations 
headed Cetin and McKinnon. The two ministers held a joint news 
conference after the talks. Cetin said that bilateral and 
regional relations were discussed at the talks and that the 
situation in Middle East, Iraq, the Balkans and the Caucasus 
were discussed within this framework. Cetin stated that if the 
tragedy in Bosnia-Herzegovina does not end then similar 
incidents might occur in other regions in the world as well, 
adding that the Armenian occupation of part of Azerbaijani 
territory constitutes such an example. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

