<F P=102>  OW0203091694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0906 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0203091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 2 KYODO -- U.S. Undersecretary of 
State Joan Spero will visit Japan next week for talks with 
Japanese officials on bilateral trade affairs, a senior Foreign 
Ministry official said Wednesday [2 March]. 
  Spero, a top State Department official in charge of economic 
affairs, is likely to arrive in Japan before or around March 9, 
when U.S. State Secretary Warren Christopher is also due in 
Japan, the official said. 
  She is likely to hold talks with Deputy Foreign Minister 
Koichiro Matsuura, a top negotiator in the bilateral trade 
"framework" talks, he said. 
  Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa and President Bill Clinton 
met on February 11 in Washington but failed to reach accord on 
the framework talks. 
  Christopher is scheduled to visit Japan between March 9 and 
11 on his three-nation Asia-Pacific trip. 
  It is not yet clear whether Spero will accompany Christopher 
to Japan or will make the trip separately, the official said. 

