  [Excerpts] This morning, Souban Salitthilat, acting 
minister of foreign affairs of the Lao People's Democratic 
Republic [LPDR], met and held talks with Ajit Singh, secretary 
general of the ASEAN, at the Vang Sadet guest house in 
Vientiane. Ajit Singh is currently on his first visit to the 
LPDR. The visit is scheduled from 27 February to 2 March. The 
meeting and talks proceeded in a very cordial atmosphere. 
  On this occasion, Souban Salitthilat informed the ASEAN 
secretary general of the (?domestic situation in Laos) and noted 
the possibility of expanding cooperation between Laos and the 
ASEAN group [words indistinct]. The two sides also discussed 
other issues of common interest. They particularly discussed 
means of effectively promoting and expanding the relations and 
cooperation between Laos and the ASEAN member countries in the 
immediate future. 
  ASEAN Secretary General Ajit Singh and his wife arrived in 
Vientiane at noon on 27 February. They were accorded a warm 
welcome by Souban Salitthilat, acting minister of foreign 
affairs, and his wife. They were also welcomed upon their 
arrival by members of diplomatic corps of the ASEAN countries 
along with a number of (?high-ranking cadres). [passage omitted] 
  The visit to Laos by the ASEAN secretary general on this 
occasion is considered a good sign for the friendly relations 
between Laos and the countries of the ASEAN group. The visit 
has also contributed to creating an atmosphere of mutual 
understanding between the countries in the region. 

