<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Japanese Telecommunications Investment Sought </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0203080994 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0203080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Communications Minister Phinit Charusombat 
has reported on the outcome of his meeting with Japan's deputy 
international trade and industry minister in Tokyo yesterday. 
  The Thai deputy minister informed his Japanese counterpart 
of 
the latest progress and developments in telecommunications in 
Thailand and told him of the government's policy of allowing the 
private sector to invest more in the telecommunications field. 
As a result, the government has promoted free trade competition 
in line with Thailand's commitment to GATT. 
  Phinit said that Japan and Thailand have cooperated with 
each 
other in developing telecommunications activities in both the 
government and private sectors. Japanese companies have invested 
several billion baht in the communications field in Thailand. 
Given that Thailand is currently more prepared for foreign 
investors, Japan's international trade and industry ministry is 
therefore asked to encourage Japanese investors to invest more 
in Thailand, especially in the telecommunications field, so that 
the telecommunications services in Thailand and Japan will 
develop on an equal basis. 

</TEXT>

