<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies U.S. Previewed GATT Schedule </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203065194 Seoul YONHAP in English 0625 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203065194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 2 (YONHAP) -- The Foreign Ministry 
denied press reports Wednesday that South Korea handed over its 
Uruguay Round country schedule to the United States before even 
submitting it to the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade 
(GATT). 
  "We are not obligated to show the country schedule to the 
U.S. side, and we have not done so," a ministry official said. 
The vernacular daily KUNGMIN ILBO quoted Economic Planning Board 
and Agriculture Ministry officials as saying that the country 
schedule was given to the United States even before it was 
revealed domestically. Seoul had waited to reveal the schedule 
to GATT headquarters until after the major trade negotiators -- 
the United States, Japan, Canada and the European Union -- 
handed in their plans. 
  Officials here were analyzing the U.S. country schedule and 
initially agreed that revision of the original draft was 
unnecessary. They said Seoul may present its schedule as early 
as Thursday. 

</TEXT>

