<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Revival of N-S Nuclear Committee Sought </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203053694 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO in Korean 2 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Pak Ui-chun] </F>
  [Text] Considering the operation of the North-South Joint 
Nuclear Control Committee [JNCC] a must to resolution of the 
North Korean nuclear issue by the North and South, the 
government has decided to officially propose resuming the 
committee's operation to North Korea when special envoys are 
exchanged between the North and South sometime this month. 
  A government official on 2 March said: "It is very important 
to operate the JNCC at a present stage to independently resolve 
North Korea's nuclear issue and to realize the denuclearization 
on the Korean peninsula," and added "the government intends to 
suggest this matter to the North side when special envoys are 
exchanged." 
  He also disclosed that: "As soon as a working-level contact 
for the exchange of special envoys is over, the steps for the 
resumption of the JNCC will be extensively discussed," and 
concluded "however, it is not clear whether North Korea will 
accept our proposal." 

</TEXT>

