<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Delays Announcing Agreement With DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0103232894 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2210 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0103232894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP from Washington] </F>
  [Text] The U.S. Government had originally planned to 
announce the U.S.-DPRK agreement [habuimun] reached in their New 
York contact and to take simultaneous measures [tongsi chochi] 
according to it. However, it decided to delay the announcement 
on the simultaneous measures as North Korea proposed the 
South-North working-level contact to be held on 3 March, 
rescheduling the date we proposed earlier. 
  A high-level diplomatic source in Washington said: The U.S. 
Government planned to announce on 2 March -- as soon as the 
International Atomic Energy Agency inspection team arrived in 
Pyongyang, and South-North working-level contacts were resumed 
-- a statement on the ROK Government's consent [chiji] to 
suspension of the Team Spirit exercise and on the decision to 
hold the third round of U.S.-DPRK talks on 21 March. However, 
it has decided to postpone the announcement of all simultaneous 
measures until tomorrow [3 March] because North Korea delayed 
the South-North dialogue, breaking its promise. 
  It has been learned that the U.S. Government made this 
decision after consulting with the ROK as a result of North 
Korea breaking its promise and the United States took 
countermeasures [taeung pangan] on this. 
  Sources said: All U.S.-DPRK agreements are linked with one 
another. If, either side, the United States or North Korea does 
not implement one of the simultaneous measures, all other 
agreements will automatically be invalidated. 
  Regarding this, a senior officer of the U.S. State 
Department 
stressed again that the resumption of South-North dialogue on 
the nuclear issue by exchanging envoys of South and North Korea 
is one of the preconditions [chonje chogon] of the third round 
of U.S.-DPRK talks. 

</TEXT>

