<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports on Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203044494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0427 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203044494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Gunfiring at Frontline" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
puppets on February 28 committed a provocative gunfiring in an 
area near the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ), the frontline area, 
getting on the nerves of the North, according to military 
sources. 
  They fired rifle bullets and shells into areas adjacent to 
the DMZ from Chorwon county, South Korean Kangwon Province and 
Paju and Yonchon counties, Kyonggi Province. 
  In another development, they staged ground strike, ground 
attack support and airlifting exercises against the northern 
half of Korea in the skies above Kosong County, South Korean 
Kangwon Province, and Yonchon, Paju and Hwachon of Kyonggi 
Province with the mobilisation of formations of fighter planes, 
helicopter gunships and transport helicopters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

