<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group Denunciation of ROK Rights Record Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0103062294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0103062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 1 (KCNA) -- The Council of Lawyers 
for Democratic Society in South Korea recently held a forum on 
human rights and unanimously contended that nothing has been 
improved in the situation of human rights since the appearance 
of the Kim Yong- sam regime. 
  NODONG SINMUN today says this is only too natural a 
condemnation of the traitor Kim Yong-sam's "civilian" fascist 
rule. 
  Though the traitor has advertised "reforms" as if he would 
bring some "changes" to South Korea, and made brag of his 
administrative "achievements" after his assumption of office, 
the reality shows that the "civilian" regime is violating human 
rights more harshly than the preceding military dictatorial 
regimes, the analyst says, and goes on: 
  The traitor has refused to abolish the notorious "National 
Security Law," a legacy of the military dictatorship, and 
expanded and strengthened such repressive tools as the 
"security planning board" and the "secret affairs command." 
  After rising to power, the Kim Yong-sam group began brutally 
suppressing the righteous desire of the students and people for 
independence, democracy and reunification and mercilessly 
cracking down on the struggle of the workers and peasants for 
their vital rights, branding it as "collective egoism" and 
"illegal riot." It has also put down the struggle of workers for 
a wage hike by setting in-motion even the "emergency arbitration 
power," which the preceding military dictators had not dared to 
employ. 
  Noting that the South Korean people have keenly felt that 
with the Kim Yong-sam traitorous clique as sly as fox left in 
power, they cannot feel ease even a moment but will undergo 
greater misfortunes and sufferings, the analyst says they will 
bring him to justice without fail. 

</TEXT>

