<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Nuclear Tests on Bikini Marked </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203055994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0439 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203055994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Lesson of Bikini" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- The test explosion of a 
newly-made U.S. H-bomb on the Bikini forty years ago on March 1 
has left the lesson that nuclear holocaust must not be inflicted 
upon humanity again and a powerful struggle must be waged to get 
rid of the constant nuclear threat, says MINJU CHOSON in a 
by-lined article today dedicated to day of Bikini. 
  Pointing out that the imperialist reactionary forces are 
still threatening mankind with nuclear weapons going against the 
trend of the present times, the article says: 
  The United States continues the test and production of 
nuclear weapons and is bringing dark clouds of nuclear war, 
having deployed nuclear weapons and their means of delivery in 
many parts of the world. 
  Nuclear threat is coming from Japan, too. It is no secret 
that Japan, the only nuclear victim in the world, is now working 
with extra zeal to become a nuclear power. Japan which has 
stockpiled large quantities of plutonium can turn into a nuclear 
power any moment. The outcries of the Japanese ruling quarters 
over the DPRK's "nuclear issue" are intended to justify their 
moves to be a nuclear power. 
  It is a common task of the world people to build a peaceful 
new world free from nuclear weapons by smashing the nuclear war 
moves of the imperialist reactionary forces. 
  The world peaceloving people should build a peaceful world 
without nuclear weapons with a united struggle. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

