<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Communist Party Supports Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0103222894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1505 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0103222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 1 (KCNA) -- The political and 
public circles of the world express positive support to the 
statement of a spokesman of the DPRK Foreign Ministry on the 
nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula. 
  The Council of the Union of Communist Parties-the Communist 
Party of the Soviet Union adopted a statement at its plenary 
meeting held on February 12 and 13. 
  The statement expressed support and solidarity for the 
principled stand made clear by a spokesman of the DPRK Foreign 
Ministry in a statement and the sincere efforts of the DPRK 
Government for the solution of the nuclear issue of the Korean 
peninsula. The statement vehemently condemned the U.S. 
Administration and reactionaries for creating tensions in the 
Korean peninsula and the world. 
  Chairman of the National Liberation War Veterans Committee 
of 
Zimbabwe Charles Hongwe said in a statement on February 12 that 
the United States must take a sincere stance for a solution to 
the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula through negotiation 
and immediately stop scheming to isolate and stifle the DPRK. 
  The Political Department of the Palestine Liberation 
Organisation in a statement on February 14 said that the nuclear 
issue on the Korean peninsula is not a matter to be solved by 
force. "If the United States is really willing to resolve the 
nuclear issue, it should show a right position toward dialogue 
first of all," it said. 
  Chairman of the Butwal Peace Action Committee Soorya Laleit 
in a statement demand that the United States immediately drop 
its provocative scheme to deploy Patriot missiles and withdraw 
its troops and nuclear weapons from South Korea without delay. 
  Members of the Russian Communist Workers' Party and the 
"Labouring Russia" Movement and Moscow citizens held a 
demonstration in front of the U.S. Embassy in Moscow on February 
6. The protesters staged a sit-down against the U.S. 
interference and aggressive moves in Korea in front of the U.S. 
Embassy, holding slogan boards reading "United States, take 
hands off socialist Korea", "Glory to the heroic Korean people" 
and so on. 
  They handed over to the U.S. Embassy a "letter of protest 
against the U.S. moves of aggression against the DPRK" in the 
name of the Russian Communist Workers' Party and the "Labouring 
Russia" Movement. 

</TEXT>

