<F P=103> SK0203105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
observe the 17th anniversary of the proclamation of the great 
Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya. 
  The Libyan people have made strenuous efforts to build a new 
society, firmly defending the gains of the September first 
revolution under the banner of anti-imperialist independence, 
MINJU CHOSON in a signed article says, and continues: 
  The Libyan people who set store by the national dignity and 
sovereignty of the country are accelerating economic 
construction, while increasing the country's defence capability 
to cope with the aggressive moves of imperialists. 
  Libya, pursuing the non-alignment policy externally, is 
striving for the unity and cohesion of the Arab nation. 
  The two peoples of Korea and Libya established and have 
favourably developed their friendly relations. Their mutual 
support and cooperation have been conducive to the building of a 
new society. 
  The Korean people believe that the friendly and cooperative 
relations between Korea and Libya will further expand and 
develop in the future, and hope the Libyan people new success in 
the efforts to build a prosperous new society. 
  NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined article says the Libyan people 
are making unremitting efforts to defend the sovereignty of the 
country and build a new society, smashing the manoeuvrings of 
imperialists against Libya. 

</TEXT>

