<H3> <TI>   Works of Kim Chong-il Reportedly Studied Abroad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203110194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1015 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- Famous works of the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il have been disseminated and 
studied in different countries. 
  A seminar on his work "Abuses of Socialism are Intolerable" 
was held by the British group for the study of the revolutionary 
activities and works of Comrade Kim Il-song. 
  Chief of the group Dermot Hudson in his report stressed: 
  This work of Comrade Kim Chong-il is a militant banner for 
frustrating the anti-socialist strategy of the imperialists and 
defending and advancing the cause of socialism. He in his work 
lays bare the falsehood and reactionary nature of the 
anti-socialist vile propaganda made by the imperialists and 
reactionaries. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il has developed and enriched the idea and 
theory on socialism and brought the essential superiority of 
socialism to capitalism into full play in Korea, so that mankind 
may confidently advance along the road of socialism with a 
beacon of hope. 
  Under his wise leadership the cause of socialism will make a 
long drive. 
  Seminars on the same work were held by the group for the 
study of the chuche idea of the Marien Ngouabi University of the 
Congo, chuche idea study groups of Guyana and Calcutta 
University of India. 
  Seminars on his work "Our Socialism Centred on the Masses 
Shall Not Perish" were held by the committee for the study of 
Kimilsongism of youth in Karachi, Pakistan, the Murewa, 
Zimbabwe, group for the study of the chuche idea and the group 
for the study of the chuche idea of the Administration and 
Development College in Mjumbe, Morogoro, Tanzania and a seminar 
on his work "The Historical Lesson in Building Socialism and the 
General Line of our Party" by the Uttar Pradesh State, India, 
committee for the study of the chuche idea. 

</TEXT>

