<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poems Praising Kim Chong-il Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0103223594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1515 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0103223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, march 1 (KCNA) -- Many poems praising the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il have been created in the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  From February last year to the end of January this year, the 
literary and art press group and the Kumsong Youth Publishing 
House carried more than 200 of poems written by poets and 
working people of different strata in various publications. 
  In this period, poets of the Korean writing group created 
"Son of the People", "Pride of Korea", "One Big Family" and many 
other poems of high ideological and artistic value. 
  A lyric "Son of Paektu" tell about the Korean people's great 
pride and honor of having the iron-willed brilliant commander 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, a peerless great man and great son of the 
country produced by Mt. Paektu. 
  Poets of the group recently held a poem recitation meeting 
in 
front of the old home at the Mt. Paektu secret camp with "With 
the Old Home at Mt. Paektu Secret Camp", "May the Chong-il Peak 
Shine Through Generations", "Strides of Great Man" and other 
poems they had recently written on the occasion of the birthday 
of Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  Poems praising the peerless great man have been widely 
created by working people, youth and students and People's Army 
soldiers. 
  In December last year, Yi In-mo, the incarnation of faith 
and 
will, composed poems "Bout my Destiny", "Thinking About Love" 
and "Laudatory Song of Faith and Will" and presented them to the 
dear leader. 
  In the poems, Yi In-mo tells about his strong ideological 
feeling that Korea's cause of socialism, the revolutionary 
cause of chuche, is invincible as long as there is the wise 
guidance of dear Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  Rim Chang-su in Jongpmhong County, South Hamgyong Province, 
and Kim Chae-song in Unjon County, North Phyongan Province, 
wrote lyrics "The Sun of the Nation, The Heaven of Mankind" and 
"Let us Sing of Our Mother Party" which tell about the unanimous 
resolution and will of the Korean people to hold in high esteem 
as the great sun Comrade Kim Chong-il who looks after and 
protects the destiny, future and hope of the Korean nation and 
to remain loyal and filial to him. 
  Poems created among People's Army soldiers sing of their 
great pride and honor of having their supreme commander in the 
person of Comrade Kim Chong-il who is possessed of rare 
intelligence and outstanding strategy, ever-victorious 
commandership iron will and matchless grit and warm love of 
soldiers, and reflect their unshakable faith and will to 
resolutely safeguard him with arms. 
  Several hundred pieces of poem including "He is Our Supreme 
Commander", "Highest Glory to the Revolutionary Armed Forces of 
Chuche" and "We Serve Comrade Supreme Commander!" have been 
created among People's Army soldiers in the last two years alone. 

</TEXT>

