<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on National Agricultural Meeting </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kang Song-san Attends Ceremony </H4>
<F P=102> SK0203055694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0434 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- Official commendations 
and gifts were awarded to participants in the National 
Agricultural Conference with a due ceremony here on March 1. 
  Present at the ceremony were Premier Kang Song-san and Vice- 
President Yi Chong-ok who are members of the Political Bureau of 
the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and other 
party and state cadres. 
  Honorary titles were awarded to the units which had made 
palpable successes in the socialist rural construction and grain 
and other agricultural production through their vigorous efforts 
to implement the "Theses on the Socialist Rural Question in Our 
Country", and letters of commendation of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song to 27 participants in the conference, the 
commemoration order of the 30th anniversary of publication of 
the rural theses to 9,993 and order of national flag second 
class to 139. 
  And commendations of the great leader President Kim Il-song 
were awarded to 340 people and gifts to the entire participants. 

</TEXT>

