<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on National Agricultural Meeting </TI></H3>
<H4>   Implementation of Program Urged </H4>
<F P=102> SK0103072694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0525 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0103072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 1 (KCNA) -- "For the ultimate 
solution of the rural question under the banner of the socialist 
rural theses," the letter sent by the great leader Comrade Kim 
Il-song to the national agricultural conference, is a programme 
of socialist rural construction in our times and a militant 
banner which makes it possible to develop in depth our 
agriculture to a higher level, says NODONG SINMUN in an 
editorial Tuesday. 
  The editorial says the historic letter of the great leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song consummates the theoretical and practical 
matters for finally solving the rural question, the most 
difficult question in socialist construction, by dynamically 
accelerating rural construction along the road indicated by the 
rural theses. 
  The editorial quotes the respected leader Comrade Kim 
Il-song 
as saying: 
  "If we consolidate the position we have already taken up and 
launch a new battle by making more strenuous efforts, we will 
win a historic victory in the solution of the rural question, 
the most difficult question in the building of socialism." 
  The work, it notes, is a militant banner that instills into 
the minds of our agricultural working people and other people 
the conviction of the might of the chuche-based system of the 
socialist rural economy and the invincibility of the 
Korean-style socialism and that powerfully encourages them in 
the work for consolidating and developing them; it is a highly 
important guideline in effecting a new revolutionary turn in our 
rural economy and in all sectors of agricultural production. 
  The work is a famous work that has further developed and 
enriched the revolutionary theory of the working class on 
socialist and communist construction with new and unique 
contents, the editorial points out, and goes on: 
  It is of weighty significance in the development of the 
revolutionary theory of rural construction that the great leader 
in this work gave a comprehensive exposition of the principle, 
ways and time of the conversion of cooperative property to 
all-people property. The theories of creating conditions for 
the switchover of cooperative property to all-people property, 
conducting it with the county as a unit, and correctly defining 
the forms and ways of the switchover and other theories 
propounded in the work light the path of finally solving the 
rural question without the slightest deviation. 
  The great leader's work is a powerful weapon in refuting the 
sophism of the imperialists that socialism cannot find a 
solution to the rural question and smashing all descriptions of 
opportunist tendencies of removing the revolutionary principle 
of the working class in rural construction. 
  The editorial calls upon all the party members and other 
working people to make a deep-going study of the profound idea 
and theories laid down in the work, fully grasp them and develop 
in depth the three revolutions, ideological, technical and 
cultural, in compliance with the requirements of socialist rural 
construction on a new, higher stage. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

