<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Arranges Rural Theses Banquet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0103112094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1041 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0103112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 1 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song arranged a grand banquet at the Kumsusan 
Assembly Hall today in celebration of the victory of "theses on 
the socialist rural question in our country". 
  When President Kim Il-song appeared in the banquet hall amid 
the playing of the welcome music, the entire participants 
enthusiastically welcomed him with a stormy applause. 
  Kang Song-san, member of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and premier of 
the Administration Council, made a speech at the banquet. 
  Present there were O Chin-u, member of the Presidium of the 
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party 
of Korea and minister of People's Armed Forces; Yi Chong-ok, Pak 
Song- chol and Kim Yong-chu, members of the Political Bureau of 
the WPK Central Committee and vice-presidents; and other party 
and state cadres, management officials of co-op farms and state 
farms, secretaries of the party committees, leading officials of 
state agricultural enterprises and factories and enterprises 
serving agriculture, agricultural scientists and model workteam 
heads, sub- workteam heads and farmers of cooperative farms. 

</TEXT>

