<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mining Industry Reportedly Exceeds Feb Goals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0203055394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0431 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 2 (KCNA) -- Industrial 
establishments of Korea overfulfilled their February plans and 
are expanding the achievements. 
  The Anju District coal mining complex topped its February 
target on all indices by introducing a new coal cutting method. 
It continues boosting production in March. 
  The Chilli coal mine doubled production in February compared 
with the same month of last year by introducing a new blasting 
method. 
  The Tokchon District coal mining complex carried out its 
February assignments for capital tunnelling at 100.5 nercent, 
preparatory tunnelling at 101.3 percent, slope pit tunnelling at 
101.3 percent, pit concreting at 112.8 percent and coal output 
at 101.8 percent as of February 27. 
  The Changjagang Power Station fulfilled its February plan 
three days ahead of schedule and the Chagang provincial combined 
general bureau of forestry produced over 10,000 more cubic 
metres of timber in February as against the same period of last 
year. 
  The Songsan mine surpassed its February goal by 48 percent 
in 
terms of output value and by 27 percent in kind. It is carrying 
out its daily quotas at 130 to 150 percent in march. The mine 
fulfilled its January plan in a matter of 14 days. 
  February plans were also overfulfilled by the Myongchon 
District coal mining complex, the General Bureau of Harbour 
Works, the Pyongyang Municipal General Bureau of Garment 
Industry and many other units, which are keeping a high rate of 
production in March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

