<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mongolian President Arrives, Meets Khamtai </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2802135394 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2802135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In response to an invitation from His Excellency 
[H.E.] Nouhak Phoumsavan, president of the Lao People's 
Democratic Republic [LPDR], H.E. Mongolian President 
Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, his wife, and a high-level Mongolian 
delegation arrived in Vientiane by special plane at 1630 today 
for a four-day official friendship visit to our country. 
  H.E. Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, his wife, and the delegation 
were welcomed upon their arrival at Wattai Airport by H.E. 
President Nouhak Phoumsavan and his wife; H.E. National Assembly 
Chairman Saman Vi-gnaket; H.E. Khamphoui Keoboualapha, deputy 
prime minister and chairman of the Planning and Cooperation 
Committee; H.E. Vientiane Municipality Governor Boun-gnang 
Volachit; H.E. Phao Bounnaphon, minister attached to the Prime 
Minister's Office; H.E. Thongdam Chanthaphon, minister attached 
to President's Office; H.E. Trade Minister Sompadit Volasan; 
H.E. Thongsavat Boupha, deputy minister of foreign affairs; H.E. 
Khamphai Latsami, deputy minister of public health; and H.E. 
Chaleun Valinthalasak, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of the LPDR to Mongolia, along with a number of 
dignitaries and Vientiane residents. [passage omitted] 
  Accompanying H.E. President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat and his 
delegation on this visit to the LPDR are H.E. Foreign Affairs 
Minister Tserenpilyn Gombosuren; H.E. Tsebegmidiin Tsogt, 
minister of trade and industry; H.E. Toytigiyn Tomorhuleg, 
ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary of Mongolia to the 
LPDR [passage indistinct]. 
  Later, H.E. President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat and his 
delegation met with H.E. LPDR Prime Minister Khamtai Siphandon 
at the Prime Minister's Office. At 1900, H.E. Punsalmaagiym 
Ochirbat, along with his wife and delegation, attended a banquet 
in their honor hosted by H.E. President Nouhak Phoumsavan and 
his wife at the National Assembly Hall in the capital, Vientiane. 

</TEXT>

