<H3> <TI>   Reaction to UK Press Allegations Continues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Defense Minister on British Frigates </H4>
<F P=102> BK0303092494 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303092494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said the 
purchase of the Royal Malaysian Navy's frigates worth 1.2 
billion ringgit from a British company was a genuine 
value-for-money buy. Denying an allegation that the government 
had been ripped off by the company Yarrow Shipbuilders, he said 
as far as the armed forces was concerned, the purchase was 
within the requirement. 
  He said the contractor had quoted a figure of 1.4 billion 
ringgit, which was in line with the minister's evaluation of the 
market value. The proposed purchase included the weaponry 
systems fitted on the ship, which was almost equivalent to the 
type (Silver Creek) frigate, a bigger class frigate (?acquired) 
by Malaysia. 
  When the contract was signed, the pound sterling was at 3.7 
against the ringgit. Datuk Sri Najib said he had no (?clues) to 
seek legal action on the allegation made by the British 
opposition MP Stephen Byers, that Yarrow had ripped off the 
government. He was speaking to reporters after the ministry's 
[words indistinct] in Kuala Lumpur. 

</TEXT>

