<H3> <TI>   Radio: 25 Feb Battambang Attack Repulsed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0303023694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303023694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Some days ago, puppets of communist Vietnam and the 
two-headed government gathered troops at Kouk Tbeng and Ta Sanh 
villages on south Sisophon battlefield [Battambang Province] in 
an attempt to attack and rob people's property and attack 
Democratic Kampuchea in the liberated zones. 
  On 25 February, National Army of Democratic Kampuchea forces 
and the people joined together, attacked, and routed these 
troops. As a result: 
  1. More than 10 AK rifles, over 300 hand grenades, five SK 
rifles, three RPD guns, an M-18 gun, two B-40 rocket launchers, 
10 rucksacks, 10 field radios, and other materiel were seized; 
  2. Eighteen of the attacking troops were killed and 15 
others wounded; more than 10 AK rifles, [words indistinct] were 
destroyed. Three soldiers were captured. 

</TEXT>

