<H3> <TI>   IAEA Inspection of DPRK Sites Begins 3 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303135394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1339 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, March 3 KYODO -- A seven-member team began 
Thursday [3 March] inspecting North Korea's nuclear facilities, 
a spokesman for the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) 
said. The inspection of seven declared facilities will last 
through March 15, the spokesman said. The IAEA inspection team 
arrived in Pyongyang on Tuesday. The inspections followed an 
agreement reached by the United States and North Korea last 
Friday at a working-level meeting in New York that Pyongyang 
fully implement IAEA inspections of its seven declared nuclear 
plants. 

</TEXT>

