<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cultural Cooperation Pact Initialed With PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0303071294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0135 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 3 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and China 
initialed a cultural cooperation pact in Seoul Thursday to 
promote exchanges in education, academia, the arts, mass media, 
youth activities and sports. Yi Won-yong, director-general of 
cultural affairs at the Foreign Ministry, and Wu Chunde, 
director for cultural relations at the Chinese Ministry of 
Culture, inked the accord in Seoul. 
  The pact will be formally signed later this month by the two 
nations' foreign ministers during South Korean President Kim 
Yong-sam's state visit to Beijing. The agreement includes 
cooperation across a wide range of cultural activities as well 
as exchanges of information and know-how on protecting relics. 
The two countries intend to form a joint committee to determine 
specific means of cooperation. 

</TEXT>

