<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-042 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official on Burmese Handling of Fishermen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0303031294 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0000 GMT 
3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0303031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Plotprasop Suratsawat, the Fishery 
Department director, in the past three months Burma has sunk 50 
to 70 Thai fishing boats and caused the deaths of over 200 Thai 
fishermen by gunshot wounds or drowning. A number of Burmese 
fishermen have also lost their lives. 
  Plotprasop said that although Thai fishing boats were guilty 
of fishing in Burmese waters, Burmese punishment was excessive. 
The Burmese Government is asked to look into the matter. There 
should be a standard in punishing guilty Thai fishing boats, not 
applying violent methods. It is believed that the violent 
action was committed by low ranking sailors who were patrolling 
the sea. In any event, Thailand has asked to negotiate the 
fishing problem with the Burmese Government but there has been 
no response to date. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

