<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Rebel Activities for 19-25 February </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0203054194 </F>
<F P=103> BK0203054194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a roundup of reports 
of Philippine rebel activities from Philippine media monitored 
by Bangkok Bureau between 19 and 25 February. Source 
information is given in parentheses at the end of each item. 
  19 February 
  A New People's Army leader, Lodelo Neon, and his wife, 
Imnas Marcos, were captured by the military in the village of 
Basilio, Roxas Municipality, Kalinga Apayao Province. Neon was 
a platoon leader of Section 2 of the Dr. Juan Escandor 
operational command. (Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 19 Feb, 
p 25) 
  20 February 
  The Armed Forces of the Philippines Civil Relations 
Service reports that the Philippine Army captured a suspected 
New People's Army propagandist in Davao del Norte. (Manila 
MANILA BULLETIN in English 20 Feb, p 12) 
  Military investigators in San Miguel, Bulacan are 
investigating a report that striking employees of a firm asked 
rebels, who showed up with many guns, to intimidate management. 
(Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 20 Feb, p 12) 
  21 February: No fileworthy items monitored. 
  22 February 
  Three rebels were killed and three others captured in an 
encounter between New People's Army terrorists and Army troops 
in the heavily forested village of Mabini, Daraga Municipality, 
Albay Province. The captured rebels were identified as Blandino 
Olaybal, Angeles Avila, and Rico Limiro. (Manila MANILA 
BULLETIN in English 22 Feb, p b-8) 
  Three New People's Army rebels led by Usman Mabandos, 
alias Commander Iligan, turned over their armalite rifles to the 
Southern Command during surrender rites in Sibagat, Agusan del 
Sur. (Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 22 Feb, p b-8) 
  23-25 February: No fileworthy items monitored. 

</TEXT>

