<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Singaporean Prime Minister Visit, Talks Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Double Taxation Agreement Signed </H4>
<F P=102> BK0203134094 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0203134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Singapore and Vietnam have signed an avoidance of 
double taxation agreement to bring about more trade, investment, 
and exchange of expertise. The signing ceremony in Hanoi today 
was witnessed by Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and Prime Minister 
Vo Van Kiet. Minister of State for Finance and Communications 
Commodore Teo Chee Hean signed for Singapore, while Finance 
Minister Ho Te represented the Vietnamese Government. 
  The tax agreement will be particularly welcomed by 
Singaporeans, who have investments of some 700 million dollars 
in Vietnam. It is the latest in a series of bilateral trades 
signed since 1992 which have further boosted economic ties. 
These include shipping, trading, and investment guarantee tax. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

