<H3> <TI>   Editorial Welcomes Visit of Mongolian President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0303071894 Hanoi VNA in English 0624 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0303071894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 3 -- Mongolian President P. 
Ochirbat's visit to Vietnam is an important event which will 
contribute to further strenthening the relations of friendship 
and cooperation between Vietnam and Mongolia, says NHAN DAN in 
an editorial to welcome the Mongolian leader who is expected 
here today. 
  The editorial continues: 
  Vietnam and Mongolia have had traditional cooperation and 
friendship for more than four decades now. The Mongolian 
Government and people gave wholehearted support to the 
Vietnamese people in their struggle for national liberation in 
the past as well as in national construction and defence at 
present. Mongolia has highly appreciated the result recorded by 
the Vietnamese people in the current renovation process, and 
wished to develop its multisided cooperation with vietnam. 
During President Ochirbat's visit the Vietnamese and Mongolian 
delegations will exchange views on measures, forms and 
possibilities to promote bilateral relations.' 
  `As two developing countries where economic reforms are in 
process, Vietnam and Mongolia will contribute to speeding up the 
trend for peace and stability in the East Asian region and the 
world,' the editorial concludes. 

</TEXT>

