<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chief Delegate Discusses Contact </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0303105994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1047 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Panmunjom, March 3 (KCNA) -- The fourth working 
contact for the exchange of presidential envoys between the 
North and the South was held behind closed doors in the South 
side's portion of Panmunjom today. 
  The contact was resumed by the North side's sincere efforts 
four months after the third contact was held in October last 
year. 
  After the contact, the head of the North side's delegation 
met with home and foreign reporters on the spot and briefed them 
on its results. 
  According to him, the North side said the way of breaking 
through the difficulties smoothly and at the earliest date at a 
time when the danger of a nuclear war is menacing the nation is 
to remove the obstacles to the exchange of envoys. It urged the 
South side to stop all the large-scale nuclear war exercises 
against its dialogue partner, give up seeking an "international 
cooperation system," cancel the projected introduction of 
Patriot missiles and withdraw its remarks that it "could not 
shake hands" with its dialogue partner. 
  The South side, however, made it impossible to discuss 
working procedures concerning the exchange of envoys, repeating 
its far- fetched argument in a bid to justify its unreasonable 
stand towards dialogue. 
  The sides agreed to have the next working contact at the 
Tongil House in the North side's portion of Panmunjom on March 9. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

