<H3> <TI>   U.S. Official Cited on ROK Security Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0303001694 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2110 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0303001694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2110 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report of Christian Broadcasting 
Network in Seoul, U.S. Deputy Assistant Secretary of State 
Hubbard, in a speech made at the American University on 25 
February, called for the abolition of the National Security Law 
in South Korea. 
  Meanwhile, in a public session on 1 March, a U.S. Department 
of State spokesman confirmed that the U.S. deputy assistant 
secretary of state's remarks calling for the abolition of the 
National Security Law were made by a responsible authority and 
reveal [palkida] the U.S. official position. 
  Faced with the U.S. side's position urging the abolition of 
the National Security Law, the South Korean authorities and the 
Democratic Liberal Party went around busily reacting with 
remarks about interference in domestic affairs and so forth. 
  On the other hand, a spokesman of the opposition Democratic 
Party, said that the U.S. side's expression of its official 
position calling for the abolition of the National Security Law 
is, in terms of universal principles, rightful [tangyonhan], and 
strongly urged the authorities to abolish the National Security 
Law. 

</TEXT>

