<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement Denouncing ROK Nuclear Dumping Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0303102794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1003 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Central Committee of the South Korean National Democratic Front 
[SKNDF] (Hanminjon) released a statement on February 26 
denouncing the South Korean authorities for dumping nuclear 
waste into the East Sea of Korea, the Seoul-based radio Voice of 
National Salvation reported. 
  Noting that nuclear waste dumped into the East Sea of Korea 
by the atomic power stations of South Korea from 1986 to 1992 
amounted to 11,000 trillion becquerels, or about 100,000 curies, 
the statement said: 
  As a result, the East Sea of Korea has already turned into a 
"sea of death" and Ullung Island into the "second Bikini." 
  Such anti-national criminal acts of the South Korean 
authorities have caused wholesale deaths of fishes and 
extermination of fishes, shellfishes and cultured sea products 
in the sea off Uljin, Wolsong and Kori where atomic power 
stations are situated. A diver's wife gave birth to a brain 
immature infant and many people are dying of incurable diseases 
of unknown origin after eating fishes caught in the sea. 
  Our people are now eating radioactive materials and sleeping 
on the U.S. nuclear-powder keg which may explode at time, with 
their heads resting on pillows of nuclear waste from atomic 
power stations. 
  The South Korean authorities have kept media from reporting 
about the release of radioactive materials from atomic power 
stations in a bid to cover up their crimes. Worse still, they 
unhesitatingly perpetrated such a treacherous act as concealing 
even the dumping of 900 tons of nuclear waste into the East Sea 
of Korea by Russia with a hypocritical "investigation" in which 
they alleged "they could not find a sign of pollution." 
  The Kim Yong-sam group must immediately make public the 
amount and kinds of nuclear waste dumpted into the sea and the 
dumping places, apologize to the whole nation and promptly stop 
such an act. If it continue dumping nuclear waste into the sea, 
it can by no means escape a stern judgement by the nation and 
mankind. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

