<H3> <TI>   75th Anniversary of 1 Mar `Uprising' Celebrated </TI></H3>
<H4>   Koreans in Japan Mark Occasion </H4>
<F P=102> SK0203114694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1005 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0203114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, February 28 (KNS-KCNA) -- A central meeting 
of Korean Residents in Japan was held in Tokyo on February 28 to 
commemorate the 75th anniversary of the March 1st popular 
uprising. 
  In his report, So Man-sul, vice-chairman of the Central 
Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon), said the March 1st popular 
uprising was a nationwide anti-Japanese people's resistance in 
which the Korean people rose in struggle to retake the territory 
of their country lost to the Japanese imperialists and restore 
the national sovereignty. 
  The desire of the Korean people to achieve the sovereignty 
and independence of the country could be realised successfully 
as the respected leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song roused the 
entire fellow countrymen to accomplish the historical cause of 
national liberation, he added. 
  He recalled that the great leader formulated the "10-point 
programme of the great unity of the whole nation for the 
reunification of the country" and led the 70 million fellow 
countrymen in the struggle to achieve the national reunification 
under the banner of the great national unity. 
  He condemned the anti-DPRK campaign of the reactionaries at 
home and abroad and called upon all the people to firmly unite 
as one and fight under the banner of the great national unity to 
open a new phase of national reunification. 

</TEXT>

