<H4>   ROK President's Address Decried </H4>
<F P=102> SK0303103794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pro-Japanese Treacheries Cannot Be Concealed" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim 
Yong-sam in his "memorial address" at a "meeting held to mark 
the March 1 uprising" Tuesday described his fascist, treacherous 
regime as "an orthodox civilian" regime which has inherited the 
"legal tradition of the Shanghai Provisional Government", raving 
that it was striving to "carry forward the spirit of the March 1 
uprising". 
  An analyst of NODONG SINMUN today says it is the height of 
folly, that he, a despicable pro-American and pro-Japanese 
stooge, dared to let out such remarks, lost to shame. 
  The news analyst goes on: 
  The March First popular uprising of 1919 was an 
anti-Japanese 
resistance against the Japanese imperialists' brutal colonial 
rule and for the independence and sovereignty of the country. 
Kim Yong- sam is not entitled to talk about it, even if he had 
ten mouths. 
  His "civilian" regime is a treacherous one of "the second 
term of the sixth republic" which has inherited the tradition of 
treacheries of the "first republic" of Syngman Rhee who 
manipulated the assassination of Kim Ku, the leading figure of 
the "Shanghai Provisional Government". 
  What should not be overlooked is that the traitor Kim 
Yong-sam, allegedly commemorating the March First movement, 
insulted patriotic forerunners. 
  He drivelled that although they rose up in resistance 
against 
the Japanese imperialists' colonial rule, the forerunners did 
not intend to "discipline Japan's crimes". And he said it is 
necessary to have a correct understanding of "new Japan" of 
today and "cooperate" and "compete" with it. 
  This rigmarole of the traitor is a sermon telling the South 
Korean people to forget and not to call into question all the 
disgraces and sufferings they had undergone under the Japanese 
imperialist rule. It is a shameless jargon intended to conceal 
his pro-Japanese flunkeyist treacheries and prettify his 
clique's tieup with the Japanese reactionaries. 
  A MINJU CHOSON analyst says the traitor Kim has more 
glaringly betrayed his true color as a pro-Japanese traitor 
although he tried to conceal his treacheries through his "March 
First address". 

</TEXT>

