<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Industry Production Achievements Enumerated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0303064694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0422 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303064694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- Production is moving 
upward in different sectors of the national economy of Korea. 
  The Yongsong combined general bureau of machines 
overfulfilled its January and February plans and is keeping a 
high rate of production in March. 
  The Musan mining complex, a leading producer of iron 
headings, beat its February target at 100.1 percent and 
fulfilled the first-day quota of March at 120 percent. 
  The Sunchon district coal mining complex overfulfilled its 
February plan and is now carrying out its daily assignments at 
110 percent. 
  The Kim Chong-tae general electric locomotive enterprise has 
brought the production of electric locomotives and passenger 
coaches to an all-time high. 
  The Pyongyang spinning mill and other spinning mills topped 
the February goal of silk yarn 20 percent, greatly helping the 
Pakchon, Yongbyon and Palwon silk mills boost production. 
  The February plans were overfulfilled by the March 17 
general 
hydro-power enterprise, the October 5 general automation works, 
the Yanggang Provincial combined general bureau of forestry and 
many other units, which are now expanding the achievements in 
March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

