<H3> <TI>   `About 20,000' Refugees Await Repatriation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0203111194 Vientiane KPL in English 0923 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0203111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 2 (KPL) -- The labour and social 
welfare service of Vientiane Prefecture, on February 28, 
received from Thai Nongkhai authority 92 Lao families who 
formerly lived in Thai refugee camps. 
  The handing-over ceremony of 307 refugees, the first group 
in 
1994, at Hatsaifong District administrative office was attended 
by all sides concerned including a representative of the UNHCR 
here, Mr. Hiromi Suzuki. 
  There are still about 20,000 Lao refugees living in Thai 
camps who will return home within this programme. 

</TEXT>

