<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   N-S Talks Resume After Four-Month Break </TI></H3>
<H4>   Contact Held 3 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> SK0303012994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0114 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0303012994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Panmunjom, March 3 (YONHAP) -- South and North Korea 
met at the truce village of Panmunjom Thursday after a 
four-month break to discuss procedures for the proposed exchange 
of special envoys to resolve the North Korean nuclear question 
and other pending inter-Korean issues. 
  The fourth working-level contact, held at "peace house" on 
the southern side of the demilitarized zone, was attended by 
Song Yong-tae, chief South Korean delegate, and his North Korean 
counterpart, Pak Yong-su. 
  The two sides are meeting at Panmunjom to determine the 
date and agenda for the exchange of special envoys. The envoy 
exchange between the two Koreas was one of the conditions set in 
the U.S.-North Korean agreement worked out at their 
working-level contact in New York. 
  Pyongyang must resume dialogue with Seoul if it wants to 
hold 
a third round of high-level talks with the United States, 
tentatively slated for March 21 in Geneva. 
  With the meeting, Seoul is expected to announce the 
suspension of the joint U.S.-South Korean military exercise Team 
Spirit on condition that practical discussion toward the 
resolution of the North Korean nuclear question will be 
undertaken through the exchange of special envoys between South 
and North Korea. 

</TEXT>

