<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tokyo To Brief Spero on Market Opening Steps </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303125794 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 3 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 11 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0303125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Under Secretary of State Joan Spero (for 
International Economic Affairs), a U.S. Government official in 
charge of the Japan-U.S. framework talks, is to visit Japan on 9 
March to meet informally with his Japanese counterpart Deputy 
Foreign Minister Koichiro Matsuura. The Japan-U.S. framework 
talks, which broke down at the latest Japan-U.S. summit in 
February, are now in a "cooling-off period," (as Prime Minister 
Hosokawa has said). This is the first time that Japanese and 
American officials in charge of the talks will meet informally. 
Deputy Foreign Minister Matsuura intends to explain to U.S. 
Under Secretary of State Spero about Japan's posture to work 
voluntarily for opening the Japanese market and discuss ways to 
resume the framework talks with the American official, 
(according to a senior Foreign Ministry official). 

</TEXT>

