<H3> <TI>   Researchers Discount Sanctions Effect on DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303042294 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 3 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0303042294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 3 Mar Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] A two-day study session held at the National 
Institude for Defense Studies Research in Tokyo by Japanese and 
Russian defense researchers closed on 2 March. The session was 
part of the program for the third Japan-Russia defense study 
exchange of researchers of Japan's Defense Agency and the 
Russian Defense Ministry and Federation Armed Forces. In the 
meeting, the Russian officials presented their view on the issue 
of nuclear arms development by the DPRK (North Korea) and said 
economic sanctions against that country would have no effect. 

</TEXT>

