<H3> <TI>   Defense Agency Reviews `Optimum' Capabilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303021694 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 2 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0303021694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Agency held the first meeting of the 
"Conference on Defense Capability" with Director General Kazuo 
Aichi as its chairman on 1 March. In his speech, Aichi 
stressed: "Discussions at the council will be very important in 
deciding Japan's optimum defense capability." The Defense 
Policy Council, a private advisory body to Prime Minister 
Morihiro Hosokawa, has also started reviewing the "National 
Defense Program Outline" to study the optimum defense 
capability. The Defense Agency's study group will proceed 
independently with discussions on medium- to long-range policies. 

</TEXT>

