<H3> <TI>   Russia Recognizes Nation's Nuclear-Free Status </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203192494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1715 GMT 2 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0203192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 2 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- In 1992 
Mongolia has made the statement on becoming a nuclear free zone. 
The USA, the PRC, Great Britain, and recently France have 
announced about their respect for this status of Mongolia, is 
said in the statement of the representative of the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation of March 1. 
  I would like to note that position of the Russian side on 
this issue has been reflected in the clause 4 of the treaty on 
friendly relations and cooperation, which was signed with 
Mongolia in January 20, 1993, as follows: "The Russian 
Federation will have a respect for Mongolia's policy banning the 
stationing on her territory of foreign troops, nuclear and other 
weapons of mass annihilation, letting them through her 
territory", is said in the statement, the Ministry for External 
Relations of Mongolia informed about this today. 

</TEXT>

