<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Reviews Press for 2 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203192794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1721 GMT 2 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0203192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 2 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian press is covering widely the official visit of the 
President P. Ochirbat to the countries of Asia. The newspaper 
"ARDYN ERH" informs that the Mongolian president with his spouse 
has paid a visit to His Majesty King of Thailand Phumiphon 
Adunyadet and his spouse at their residence. P. Ochirbat and 
those accompanied him visited the ancient capital of Thailand 
Ayuttaya and the largest centre of tourism city of Pattaya. 
Speaking there at the press conference the President P. 
Ochirbat noted with satisfaction the unanimity of stands of 
Mongolia and Thailand on both the fundamental issues of 
bilateral relations and international ones. P. Ochirbat 
stressed the significance of signed during his visit to Thailand 
agreements between the two countries concerning the airline 
communications and non-visa exchange of persons with diplomatic 
and official passports. 
  In this speech the Mongolian president emphasized the 
interest of Mongolia in participating actively in the regional 
cooperation of countries of Asia. 
  The newspaper publishes the full text of the joint 
communique 
on the visit of the President of Mongolia P. Ochirbat to 
Thailand. The newspaper informs about the working trip by the 
Prime Minister of Mongolia P. Jasray to the Hobd Aymag where he 
is getting acquainted with the wintering of cattle, life and 
working conditions of herdsmen. The newspaper underlined that 
P. Jasray has displayed much interest to the work of the local 
research institute relating to the growing of oilproducing crops. 
  According to the newspaper, the constitutional court has 
considered the claims of three citizens on the breach of the 
provisions of the Constitution committed by members of the 
parliament P. Elbegdorj, D. Ganbold and S. Zorig, in reference 
to the execution by them their obligations of a party members. 
The constitutional court noticed nothing in this to be regarded 
as the violation of the Constitution. 
  The newspaper informs about the outcome of the 17 winter 
Olympic games held in Lillehammer and carries the standings of 
countries whose sportsmen succeeded to win medals. 
  The central organ of the Mongolian National Democratic Party 
(MNDP) "ERH CHOLOO" puts the statement of the General Council of 
the party on its pages. The MNDP considers that the accusations 
of corruption hurled at the leadership of the parliament and the 
Prime Minister P. Jasray instead of being considered properly 
are just being used in the interests of politicizing the current 
situation in the country. 
  According to the newspaper, the General Council of the MNDP 
acknowledged at its last sitting the impossibility for their 
party to be being represented in the parliament. 
  The committee on ensuring order of the MNDP has taken a 
decree on the necessity to improve the activities of the General 
Council and other central bodies of the party reproving strictly 
the leader of the party D. Ganbold and the General Secretary E. 
Bat-Uul. Touching upon the visit paid by the Chairman of the 
ruling Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party B. Dash-Yondon to 
Japan the newspaper is wondering whether the Japanese side 
decided to give political and moral support to this party. 

</TEXT>

